      "body" : "@luke-jr Right, but the problem there is that JSON numbers are kinda-sorta double-precision floats - matching Javascript semantics - and support for bigints is pretty spotty in libraries.\r\n\r\nAlso sipa was talking about making the number in \"difficulty\" units, with has a 2^32 factor, so you'd always wind up with floating point numbers. I haven't worked it out, but I wouldn't be surprised if double-precision floats aren't precise enough for consensus purposes.",
