      "body" : "It's not a bug, it's just a limitation of JSON - bigints just aren't standard JSON. Bitcoin internally uses a uint256, so I'm not worried about exporting exactly that even if it's in hex. (like uint256 digests...) Anyway, as I said above:\r\n\r\n\"Anyone who tries to bikeshed either the name or the format the value is returned in will regret it - I'm warning you.\"\r\n\r\n...apparently I'm not threatening looking enough. Maybe I need a leather jacket and a motorcycle?",
